leas%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20dogs%20within%20eight%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChoosing%20between%20an%20oral%20or%20topical%20flea%20control%20product%20is%20tough%20for%20some%20dog%20owners.%20There%20are%20pros%20and%20cons%20to%20each%20type%20of%20product.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20an%20oral%20preventive%20is%20a%20better%20choice.%20For%20instance%2C%20some%20dogs%20with%20sensitive%20skin%20can't%20tolerate%20spot-on%20treatments.%20%26quot%3BOral%20products%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20broad%20coverage%20to%20reach%20every%20spot%20of%20skin%20without%20the%20chance%20of%20the%20product%20being%20washed%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbhcteam.com%2Famo-team%2Fkate-crumley%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Kate%20Crumley%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20with%20Blue%20Heron%20Consulting.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20give%20the%20liver-flavored%20tablets%20with%20or%20without%20food%20once%20a%20month.%20The%20treatment%20contains%20three%20ingredients%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftodaysveterinarypractice.com%2Fpharmacology%2Fsarolaner-use-in-dogs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esarolaner%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20moxidectin%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.brief.vet%2Fweb-files%2FPVD%2Fdrupal-uploads%2Ffiles%2FPyrantel%2520Pamoate%2520pkg_combined.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epyrantel%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20provides%20an%20entire%20month%20of%20protection%20against%20more%20parasites%20than%20any%20other%20oral%20product.%20Simparica%20TRIO%20is%20also%20safe%20for%20some%20of%20the%20youngest%20puppies%20and%20smallest%20dogs.%20It%20requires%20a%20prescription%20from%20your%20veterinarian%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20negative%20heartworm%20test.%20It%20should%20be%20used%20with%20caution%20in%20dogs%20with%20a%20history%20of%20neurologic%20disorders%20such%20as%20seizures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20for%20young%20puppies%3Cp%3EFleas%20should%20be%20eliminated%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%20for%20heavily%20infested%20dogs%2C%20especially%20young%20puppies.%20Available%20without%20a%20prescription%2C%20Capstar%20for%20Dogs%20is%20the%20only%20flea%20control%20product%20safe%20for%20puppies%20as%20young%20as%204%20weeks%20and%20weighing%20at%20least%202%20pounds.%20With%20other%20topical%20and%20oral%20flea%20control%20products%2C%20puppies%20must%20be%20at%20least%208%20weeks%20old%20and%20sometimes%20older.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20active%20ingredient%20in%20Capstar%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftodaysveterinarypractice.com%2Fparasitology%2Fpractical-parasitologythe-flea-infested-pet-overview-current-products%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enitenpyram%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20works%20within%2030%20minutes%20and%20kills%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcapstarpet.com%2Fproducts%2Fcapstar-nitenpyram-oral-flea-treatment-for-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E90%25%20of%20adult%20fleas%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20dogs%20in%20as%20little%20as%20four%20hours.%20Its%20protection%20against%20fleas%20lasts%20only%2024%20hours%2C%20but%20it%20is%20safe%20to%20give%20daily%20if%20necessary.%20Daily%20dosing%20is%20helpful%20for%20young%20puppies%20that%20might%20not%20be%20old%20enough%20to%20use%20an%20oral%20or%20spot-on%20product%20that%20offers%20long-term%20protection.%20Owners%20should%20follow%20up%20with%20a%20flea%20control%20product%20that%20provides%20a%20month%20or%20more%20of%20protection%20once%20the%20puppy%20is%20old%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20collar%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoresto-flea-tick-collars-linked-to-animal-deaths-human-injuries-2021-3%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMarch%202021%20investigation%20by%20USA%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20reported%201%2C700%20animal%20deaths%20and%20other%20adverse%20reactions%20linked%20to%20Seresto%20flea%20collars.%20It's%20unknown%20if%20the%20EPA-approved%20pesticides%20used%20in%20the%20collar%20caused%20these%20incidents.%20You%20can%20read%20more%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20Seresto%20collars%20in%20our%20FAQs.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlea%20collars%20were%20once%20the%20main%20option%20for%20flea%20control%2C%20but%20most%20don't%20offer%20the%20same%20level%20of%20protection%20as%20the%20best%20flea%20treatments%20for%20dogs%20available%20in%20topical%20and%20oral%20forms.%20One%20noteworthy%20flea%20collar%20is%20the%20Seresto%20Flea%20and%20Tick%20Collar%20for%20Dogs%2C%20which%20uses%20sustained-release%20technology%20to%20provide%20eight%20months%20of%20continuous%20protection%20against%20adult%20fleas%2C%20flea%20larvae%2C%20four%20species%20of%20ticks%2C%20chewing%20lice%2C%20and%20mange%20mites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20topical%20spot-on%20and%20oral%20preventives%20are%20the%20most%20effective%20flea%20control%20for%20dogs%2C%20but%20the%20Seresto%20collar%20might%20be%20a%20good%20option%20in%20certain%20situations.%20Dr.%20Kelley%20Lay%2C%20a%20relief%20veterinarian%20based%20in%20Nashville%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20says%20that%20traditional%20flea%20and%20tick%20collars%20are%20generally%20not%20very%20effective.%20She%20has%20even%20seen%20allergic%20reactions%20and%20other%20issues%20with%20some%20of%20them.%20However%2C%20she%20has%20found%20the%20Seresto%20collar%20safe%20and%20effective%20and%20recommends%20it%20to%20clients%20with%20pets%20who%20don't%20tolerate%20topical%20or%20oral%20flea%20and%20tick%20preventives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20collar%20is%20nongreasy%2C%20odor-free%2C%20lightweight%2C%20and%20adjustable%20for%20dogs%20of%20all%20sizes.%20It%20can%20be%20worn%20alongside%20your%20dog's%20regular%20collar%20and%20has%20a%20two-step%20safety%20system%20to%20keep%20your%20dog%20safe%20if%20the%20collar%20gets%20caught%20on%20something.%20The%20collar's%20active%20ingredients%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fparasitesandvectors.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2F1756-3305-5-102%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimidacloprid%20and%20flumethrin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20released%20in%20low%20concentrations%20over%20your%20dog's%20skin%20and%20coat%20to%20kill%20fleas%20and%20ticks%20on%20contact%20%E2%80%94%20parasites%20do%20not%20need%20to%20bite%20your%20dog%20for%20the%20collar%20to%20work.%20It%20kills%20100%25%20of%20fleas%20within%2024%20hours%20of%20placing%20the%20collar%20on%20your%20dog.%20You%20don't%20need%20to%20remove%20this%20water-resistant%20collar%20during%20swimming%20or%20bathing%20with%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-shampoo%5C%22%3Ebest%20dog%20shampoos%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20shampoo%3Cp%3EOur%20top%20pick%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-flea-tick-shampoo-dogs%5C%22%3Ebest%20flea%20and%20tick%20shampoo%20for%20dogs%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20Adams%20Plus%20Flea%20and%20Tick%20Shampoo.%20In%20addition%20to%20killing%20fleas%2C%20flea%20eggs%20and%20larvae%2C%20ticks%2C%20and%20lice%20for%20up%20to%2028%20days%2C%20this%20shampoo%20soothes%20skin%20that%20has%20become%20dry%20and%20irritated%20from%20flea%20bites%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fdog-scratching%5C%22%3Econstant%20scratching%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shampoo%20contains%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%2230e07200374b8a81f7b30c849dd76e2e%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftodaysveterinarypractice.com%2Fparasitology%2Fpractical-parasitologythe-flea-infested-pet-overview-current-products%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epyrethrins%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22cc2b071686b3ba6c3ad3462f33ee997f%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnpic.orst.edu%2Ffactsheets%2Fmethogen.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES-methoprene%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Precor)%20synthetic%20pesticides%20commonly%20included%20in%20flea%20and%20tick%20shampoos.%20It%20also%20contains%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%228ca876a8288b8bc93df4a0003d359484%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnpic.orst.edu%2Ffactsheets%2Fpbogen.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epiperonyl%20butoxide%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20enhance%20the%20pesticides'%20effectiveness.%20Oatmeal%20helps%20heal%20irritated%20and%20itchy%20skin%2C%20and%20the%20shampoo%20has%20a%20pleasant%20coconut%20scent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELay%20says%20that%20flea%20shampoos%20are%20fine%20to%20use%20alongside%20prescription%20flea%20control%20medications%20but%20shouldn't%20be%20considered%20the%20first%20or%20best%20line%20of%20defense%20against%20fleas.%20Veterinarian-prescribed%2C%20year-round%20flea%20prevention%20remains%20the%20gold%20standard.%20Despite%20marketing%20claims%2C%20these%20shampoos%20do%20not%20provide%20substantial%20flea%20protection%20after%20the%20bath%20and%20may%20leave%20dogs%20susceptible%20to%20repeated%20infestations.%20Some%20ingredients%20in%20shampoos%20can%20also%20irritate%20the%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20flea%20and%20tick%20prevention%20for%20dogs%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESafety%20and%20efficacy%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fconsumers%2Fconsumer-updates%2Fsafe-use-flea-and-tick-products-pets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFDA%3C%2Fa%3E-%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fpets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEPA-approved%3C%2Fa%3E%20products%20have%20undergone%20rigorous%20safety%20and%20efficacy%20testing%20before%20going%20to%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENumber%20of%20parasites%20treated%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Using%20a%20product%20that%20protects%20against%20more%20than%20just%20fleas%20is%20convenient.%20While%20your%20veterinarian%20can%20advise%20you%20on%20which%20product%20is%20best%20for%20your%20dog%2C%20we%20generally%20favor%20products%20that%20cover%20more%20parasites.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20exceptions.%20For%20instance%2C%20Capstar%20treats%20only%20fleas%2C%20but%20it%20is%20the%20only%20medicine%20available%20for%20puppies%20younger%20than%206%20weeks.%20OTC%20products%2C%20like%20Frontline%20Plus%2C%20protect%20against%20additional%20parasites%20such%20as%20ticks%20and%20lice%20but%20not%20heartworms.%20Products%20that%20treat%20heartworm%20always%20require%20a%20veterinary%20prescription.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEase%20of%20use%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20easier%20it%20is%20to%20use%20a%20product%2C%20the%20better.%20For%20example%2C%20chewable%20tablets%20are%20quick%20and%20easy%20to%20give%20your%20dog%2C%20provided%20they%20like%20the%20flavor.%20Products%20that%20require%20a%20person%20to%20wear%20gloves%20when%20they%20apply%20it%20or%20require%20the%20treated%20animal%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20children%20or%20other%20pets%20for%20a%20while%20may%20be%20a%20hassle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinimum%20age%20and%20weight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Flea%20treatments%20are%20intended%20for%20dogs%20above%20a%20minimum%20age%20and%20weight.%20Your%20options%20for%20a%20very%20young%20puppy%20will%20be%20more%20limited%20until%20they%20are%20older%20and%20weigh%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrescription%20vs.%20over-the-counter%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESome%20flea%20control%20products%20are%20available%20over%20the%20counter.%20Others%20require%20a%20prescription%20from%20your%20veterinarian.%20You%20can%20buy%20prescription%20medicines%20from%20your%20veterinarian%20or%20online%20pet%20pharmacies%20and%20stores%20like%20Chewy%2C%20Petco%2C%20and%20PetSmart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrescription%20flea%20control%20products%20typically%20cost%20more%20than%20OTC%20options%20because%20they%20protect%20against%20more%20parasites%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20deadly%20heartworms.%20Dogs%20must%20test%20negative%20for%20heartworms%20before%20starting%20a%20heartworm%20preventive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETypes%20of%20flea%20and%20tick%20medications%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThere%20are%20several%20types%20of%20treatments%2C%20including%20topical%2C%20oral%2C%20collars%2C%20shampoos%2C%20and%20sprays.%20Cost%2C%20convenience%2C%20ease%20of%20use%2C%20and%20effectiveness%20vary%20among%20these%20products.%20Your%20vet%20can%20help%20you%20determine%20the%20best%20type%20for%20your%20dog.%20We%20advise%20against%20flea%20sprays%20because%20topical%20spot-ons%20and%20oral%20products%20are%20more%20effective.%20Remember%20that%20some%20dogs%20with%20sensitive%20skin%20may%20not%20tolerate%20topical%20products.%20Crumley%20says%20that%20frequent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fhow-often-should-you-bathe-your-dog%5C%22%3Ebathing%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20swimming%20may%20also%20reduce%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20a%20topical%20product%20that%20remains%20on%20the%20skin's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENatural%20vs.%20synthetic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Our%20experts%20do%20not%20recommend%20using%20natural%20products%20instead%20of%20veterinarian-recommended%20topical%20and%20oral%20flea%20control.%20While%20natural%20treatments%20can%20deter%20fleas%20and%20ticks%2C%20they%20won't%20eliminate%20an%20infestation.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20use%20them%2C%20be%20prepared%20to%20apply%20them%20at%20least%20daily%20before%20your%20pet%20goes%20outside%20for%20the%20best%20chance%20of%20keeping%20the%20hitchhikers%20from%20latching%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Crumley.%20If%20you%20also%20have%20kitties%20at%20home%2C%20avoid%20natural%20flea%20control%20products%20containing%20essential%20oils%20because%20some%20can%20be%20toxic%20to%20cats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20pets%20in%20your%20home%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAny%20product%20labeled%20for%20use%20in%20only%20dogs%20should%20never%20be%20given%20to%20a%20cat.%20Some%20ingredients%20can%20be%20toxic%20to%20cats.%20While%20any%20dog-only%20flea%20product%20can%20harm%20felines%2C%20cats%20are%20especially%20sensitive%20to%20pyrethrins.%20If%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20safe%20product%20for%20your%20cat%2C%20check%20out%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-flea-prevention-cats%5C%22%3Ebest%20flea%20treatments%20for%20cats%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20selected%20the%20best%20flea%20treatments%20for%20dogs%3Cp%3EWe%20consulted%20two%20veterinarians%20for%20advice%20regarding%20the%20treatment%20and%20prevention%20of%20fleas%20and%20other%20parasites%20in%20dogs.%20This%20information%20guided%20our%20selection%20of%20flea%20and%20tick%20treatments%2C%20but%20our%20experts%20did%20not%20endorse%20any%20of%20the%20products%20included%20in%20this%20guide%20unless%20explicitly%20quoted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20conducted%20research%20using%20the%20quick%20product%20reference%20guide%20published%20by%20the%20independent%2C%20nonprofit%20Companion%20Animal%20Parasite%20Council.%20This%20helpful%20reference%20includes%20all%20FDA-%20and%20EPA-approved%20parasite%20control%20products%20for%20small%20animals%20along%20with%20each%20product's%20active%20ingredients%2C%20directions%20for%20how%20to%20use%20it%2C%20and%20which%20parasites%20it%20controls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFlea%20and%20tick%20medications%20for%20dogs%20FAQs%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20dogs%20really%20need%20flea%20and%20tick%20medicine%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYes.%20Not%20only%20are%20fleas%20and%20ticks%20a%20big%20nuisance%2C%20they%20also%20carry%20diseases%20that%20can%20make%20dogs%20extremely%20ill.%20Although%20you%20may%20be%20tempted%20to%20use%20parasite%20preventives%20only%20in%20spring%20and%20summer%2C%20fleas%2C%20ticks%2C%20mosquitoes%2C%20and%20intestinal%20parasites%20are%20resilient.%20Veterinarians%20recommend%20that%20dogs%20stay%20on%20broad-spectrum%20parasite%20preventives%20all%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20types%20of%20flea%20and%20tick%20medicine%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFlea%20and%20tick%20medicines%20are%20available%20as%20oral%20and%20topical%20products%2C%20collars%2C%20and%20shampoos.%20Oral%20products%20are%20chewable%20tablets%2C%20while%20topical%20products%20are%20ointments%20that%20go%20directly%20on%20the%20skin.%20Flea%20collars%20have%20fallen%20out%20of%20favor%20because%20they%20are%20less%20effective%20than%20oral%20and%20topical%20treatments.%20Shampoos%20are%20also%20less%20effective%20and%20do%20not%20provide%20long-lasting%20flea%20protection.%20These%20medicines%20are%20available%20over%20the%20counter%20or%20by%20prescription%20and%20contain%20different%20active%20ingredients%20to%20kill%20and%20repel%20fleas%20and%20ticks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20vets%20recommend%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20fleas%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20rid%20of%20fleas%20can%20take%20several%20days%20to%20weeks.%20Veterinarians%20recommend%20a%20multipronged%20approach%3A%20Kill%20the%20existing%20fleas%2C%20prevent%20new%20infestations%2C%20and%20treat%20the%20environment%2C%20both%20indoors%20and%20outside.%20If%20you%20have%20multiple%20pets%2C%20treat%20them%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20Treating%20inside%20your%20home%20involves%20vacuuming%20where%20flea%20eggs%20and%20larvae%20like%20to%20hide%2C%20such%20as%20cracks%20and%20crevices%2C%20and%20washing%20bedding%20in%20hot%20water.%20Treating%20outdoors%20involves%20eliminating%20any%20areas%20where%20fleas%20could%20hide%2C%20such%20as%20piles%20of%20leaves%20and%20tall%20grass.%20If%20this%20process%20seems%20daunting%2C%20you%20can%20hire%20a%20pest%20control%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20most%20effective%20flea%20and%20tick%20treatment%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20single%20treatment%20that%20works%20best%20for%20all%20dogs.%20The%20best%20flea%20treatments%20for%20dogs%20vary%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20including%20how%20many%20parasites%20they%20target%2C%20active%20ingredients%2C%20safety%20restrictions%2C%20and%20how%20long%20they're%20effective.%20The%20most%20desirable%20treatments%20provide%20long-lasting%20protection%2C%20target%20adult%20fleas%20as%20well%20as%20eggs%20and%20larvae%2C%20and%20are%20effective%20against%20other%20parasites%2C%20such%20as%20heartworm%20and%20intestinal%20worms.%20Your%20veterinarian%20can%20help%20you%20select%20the%20most%20appropriate%20product%20for%20your%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20kills%20fleas%20permanently%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20eliminate%20fleas%20permanently%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20do%20more%20than%20kill%20adult%20fleas.%20The%20other%20developmental%20stages%2C%20egg%20and%20larvae%2C%20must%20also%20be%20eliminated.%20Products%20that%20kill%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20fleas%20are%20the%20most%20effective.%20Year-round%20flea%20and%20tick%20treatment%20is%20also%20crucial%20to%20preventing%20future%20infestations.%20It%20may%20take%20several%20weeks%20before%20all%20the%20fleas%20are%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhich%20is%20better%2C%20NexGard%20or%20Frontline%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20NexGard%20and%20Frontline%20kill%20fleas%20at%20all%20life%20stages%2C%20plus%20ticks.%20Both%20treatments%20have%20their%20advantages.%20There%20are%20several%20Frontline%20products%3A%20Shield%2C%20Plus%2C%20and%20Gold.%20Our%20top%20choice%20for%20an%20OTC%20flea%20preventive%20is%20Frontline%20Plus%2C%20which%20also%20protects%20against%20chewing%20lice%20and%20helps%20control%20sarcoptic%20mange%20infestations.%20Compared%20to%20Frontline%20Plus%2C%20NexGard%20kills%20fleas%20more%20quickly%20(4%20hours%20versus%2012%20hours)%20and%20ticks%20(24%20hours%20versus%2048%20hours).%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20NexGard%20is%20a%20better%20choice%20for%20preventing%20the%20transmission%20of%20Lyme%20disease%20from%20ticks.%20Some%20veterinarians%20also%20use%20NexGard%20to%20treat%20mange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20safest%20flea%20and%20tick%20medicine%20for%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFlea%20and%20tick%20medicines%20are%20FDA-approved%20to%20be%20safe%20and%20effective.%20However%2C%20these%20medicines%20also%20have%20safety%20restrictions%20depending%20on%20age%2C%20weight%2C%20and%20whether%20a%20dog%20is%20pregnant%20or%20nursing.%20Some%20treatments%20also%20have%20safety%20warnings%20for%20dogs%20with%20a%20history%20of%20seizures%20or%20other%20neurologic%20disorders.%20As%20you%20evaluate%20flea%20and%20tick%20medicines%2C%20check%20the%20label%20to%20ensure%20it's%20safe%20for%20your%20dog.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20difference%20between%20prescription%20and%20OTC%20flea%20medicine%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20flea%20control%20products%20are%20sold%20over%20the%20counter%2C%20while%20others%20require%20a%20prescription.%20Prescription%20products%20typically%20cost%20more%20than%20OTC%20treatments%20because%20they%20protect%20against%20more%20parasites%2C%20including%20heartworms.%20However%2C%20OTC%20options%20can%20still%20provide%20effective%2C%20long-lasting%20treatment%20against%20fleas%20and%20other%20parasites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20I%20get%20flea%20and%20tick%20medicine%20without%20a%20vet%20prescription%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20OTC%20treatments%20are%20available%20without%20a%20prescription.%20These%20medicines%20usually%20do%20not%20protect%20against%20as%20many%20parasites%20as%20prescription%20flea%20and%20tick%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20flea%20collars%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYes.%20Flea%20collars%20work%20but%20are%20generally%20less%20effective%20than%20topical%20or%20oral%20treatments.%20Seresto%20Flea%20and%20Tick%20Collar%20for%20Dogs%20provides%20eight%20months%20of%20protection%20against%20adult%20fleas%2C%20flea%20larvae%2C%20ticks%2C%20and%20mange%20mites.%20Lay%20recommends%20flea%20collars%20for%20dogs%20that%20cannot%20tolerate%20topical%20or%20oral%20flea%20products.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20Seresto%20harmful%20to%20dogs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202021%2C%20USA%20Today%20and%20the%20Midwest%20Center%20for%20Investigative%20Reporting%20published%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Finvestigations%2F2021%2F03%2F02%2Fseresto-dog-cat-collars-found-harm-pets-humans-epa-records-show%2F4574753001%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20alleging%20that%20the%20Seresto%20flea%20collar%20is%20linked%20to%20thousands%20of%20adverse%20incidents%20in%20pets%20and%20humans.%20To%20date%2C%202%2C500%20pet%20deaths%20have%20been%20allegedly%20linked%20to%20the%20collar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElanco%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.elanco.com%2Fen-us%2Fnews%2Felanco-stands-behind-seresto%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20defending%20the%20collar's%20safety%20and%20efficacy.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.avma.org%2Fjavma-news%2F2021-05-01%2Fseresto-collars-come-under-greater-scrutiny%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Veterinary%20Medical%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20(AVMA)%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.petpoisonhelpline.com%2Fblog%2Fresponse-statement-seresto%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_b