y%20was%20banned%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20Australian%20politicians%20should%20now%20show%20solidarity%20with%20our%20Sikh%20community%2C%20who%20are%20the%20most%20visible%20targets%20of%20this%20extreme%20political%20violence.%20I%20know%20there%E2%80%99s%20apprehension%20in%20the%20Sikh%20community%20about%20their%20safety%20here%2C%20and%20I%20can%20see%20why%20they%20are%20concerned.%20We%20have%20raised%20this%20directly%20with%20security%20agencies%2C%20including%20ASIO.%20ASIO%20has%20informed%20me%20that%20there%20is%20no%20current%20identifiable%20threat%20to%20the%20Sikh%20community%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shoebridge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeeking%20a%20%E2%80%9Cclear%20and%20direct%20assurance%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20Australian%20government%20that%20proactive%20measures%20were%20being%20taken%20to%20ensure%20the%20safety%20of%20Sikhs%2C%20he%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20must%20be%20a%20public%20statement%20from%20our%20government%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India%20that%20these%20actions%20represent%20a%20gross%20breach%20of%20international%20law%20that%20offends%20Australian%20values.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20needs%20to%20state%20that%20if%20a%20similar%20plot%20occurs%20in%20Australia%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20will%20be%20taken%20as%20a%20hostile%20act%20that%20would%20fundamentally%20undermine%20our%20bilateral%20relationship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20a%20dig%20at%20Australian%20Prime%20Minister%20Anthony%20Albanese%2C%20Shoebrdige%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20one%20thing%20to%20ride%20in%20a%20golden%20chariot%20and%20venerate%20a%20foreign%20political%20leader%2C%20but%20the%20hard%20politics%20is%20when%20you%20need%20to%20put%20principles%20and%20the%20collective%20good%20of%20Australians%20ahead%20of%20a%20media%20sugar%20hit%20or%20the%20promise%20of%20a%20lucrative%20trade%20deal.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20politicians%20earn%20their%20keep.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Australian%20government%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcanada-trudeau-india-murder-us-uk-australia%5C%22%3Ebacked%3C%2Fa%3E%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20Indian%20agents%20were%20linked%20to%20the%20killing%20of%20Nijjar%2C%20asking%20India%20to%20join%20the%20investigation.%20It%20has%20not%20commented%20on%20the%20indictment%20filed%20by%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice.%20The%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Canada%2C%20Australia%20and%20New%20Zealand%20are%20part%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Five%20Eyes%E2%80%99%20intelligence%20sharing%20network%2C%20which%20informed%20Trudea%E2%80%99s%20allegation.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701870121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F06185716%2FDavid_Shoebridge_Greens_MP.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpannun-plot-australian-mp-david-shoebridge-assurance-safety-sikhs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22David%20Shoebridge%20said%20if%20the%20BJP%20administration%20is%20%26quot%3Bactively%20plotting%20to%20kill%20political%20opponents%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%2C%20just%20imagine%20what's%20happening%20in%20India%20itself%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpannun-plot-australian-mp-david-shoebridge-assurance-safety-sikhs%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20least%2021%20deaths%20and%20600%20cases%20of%20dengue%20fever%20in%20Mali%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701869107000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105788368%2Cimgsize-702774.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fat-least-21-deaths-and-600-cases-of-dengue-fever-in-mali%2Farticleshow%2F105788334.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105788334.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDengue%20fever%20is%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20Mali%2C%20where%20officials%20are%20reporting%20new%20infections%20and%20deaths%20from%20the%20virus%20this%20week.%20Mali's%20director%20general%20of%20health%20and%20public%20hygiene%2C%20Dr%20Cheick%20Amadou%20Tidiane%20Traore%2C%20told%20The%20Associated%20Press%20in%20an%20interview%20Wednesday%20that%20his%20department%20had%20counted%2021%20deaths%20and%20600%20cases%20of%20the%20virus%20as%20of%20Monday.%20Dengue%20is%20a%20viral%20infection%20spread%20by%20mosquitoes%20that%20mostly%20causes%20flu-like%20illness.%20In%20severe%20cases%2C%20the%20disease%20can%20cause%20joint%20pain%2C%20swollen%20glands%2C%20severe%20bleeding%20and%20death.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fat-least-21-deaths-and-600-cases-of-dengue-fever-in-mali%2Farticleshow%2F105788334.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reacknowledging%20Ambedkar's%20Role%20as%20the%20Architect%20of%20India's%20Constitution%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F07092014%2FDr._Babasaheb_Ambedkar_delivering_a_speech_2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ENovember%2026%20is%20celebrated%20as%20Constitution%20Day%2C%20when%20rich%20tributes%20are%20paid%20to%20the%20makers%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitution%2C%20especially%20its%20principal%20architect%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%2C%20whose%2067th%20death%20anniversary%20is%20today%2C%20December%206%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Baba%20Saheb%20Ambedkar%2C%20as%20he%20is%20popularly%20and%20affectionately%20known%2C%20lived%20only%20nine%20years%20after%20Independence%2C%20he%20left%20an%20indelible%20mark%20on%20the%20history%20of%20modern%20India%2C%20which%20inarguably%20is%20greater%20than%20his%20contribution%20during%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20when%20he%20signed%20the%20Poona%20Pact%20with%20M.K.%20Gandhi%20giving%20reserved%20seats%20to%20the%20Dalits%20after%20a%20prolonged%20struggle.%20A%20compromise%20between%20him%20and%20Gandhi%20was%20only%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20new%20life%20for%20a%20community%20that%20had%20been%20suppressed%20for%20centuries%20by%20the%20obnoxious%20caste%20system%20of%20the%20Hindu%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20India%20became%20free%2C%20Ambedkar%20was%20invited%20by%20prime%20minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20to%20join%20his%20cabinet%20and%20thus%20became%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20law%20minister.%20He%20was%20amongst%20the%20few%20non-Congress%20prominent%20personalities%20who%20were%20inducted%20into%20the%20Nehru%20cabinet.%20Others%20included%20defence%20minister%20Baldev%20Singh%20(Akali%20Dal)%2C%20Shanmukham%20Chetty%20(Justice%20Party)%2C%20and%20Syama%20Prasad%20Mukherjee%20(Hindu%20Mahasabha).%20They%20were%20opposed%20to%20the%20Congress%20party%20during%20the%20freedom%20movement.%20According%20to%20an%20eminent%20historian%2C%20this%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20extraordinary%20act%20of%20reconciliation%20for%20which%20Gandhi%20seems%20to%20be%20personally%20responsible%E2%80%9D.%20Gandhi%20was%20reported%20to%20have%20said%20that%20freedom%20had%20not%20come%20to%20a%20single%20party%20but%20to%20all%20Indians%20and%20hence%20all%20parties%20must%20be%20given%20the%20opportunity%20for%20nation-building.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20Ambedkar%20had%20to%20be%20elected%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20for%20which%20the%20Congress%20facilitated%20his%20entry%20into%20the%20Assembly%20from%20a%20safe%20seat%20in%20Bombay%20(now%2C%20Mumbai).%20Earlier%2C%20he%20was%20elected%20from%20Bengal%2C%20but%20with%20the%20division%20of%20the%20province%20after%20the%20Mountbatten%20Plan%20of%20June%203%2C%201947%2C%20he%20ceased%20to%20be%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20as%20his%20constituency%20was%20allotted%20to%20East%20Bengal%20(now%2C%20Bangladesh).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fb-r-ambedkars-fears-on-the-ecs-independence-boycott-of-minorities-are-coming-true%5C%22%3EB.R.%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20Fears%20on%20the%20EC%E2%80%99s%20Independence%2C%20Boycott%20of%20Minorities%20Are%20Coming%20True%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20biography%2C%20%3Cem%3EBabsaheb%3A%20My%20Life%20with%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Savita%20Ambedkar%20quotes%20correspondence%20between%20Rajendra%20Prasad%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%3B%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20the%20prime%20minister-elect%3B%20Sardar%20Patel%2C%20the%20home%20minister%3B%20G.%20Mavalankar%2C%20speaker%3B%20and%20B.G.%20Kher%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Bombay%20state%20to%20stress%20that%20all%20top%20Congress%20leaders%20were%20extremely%20keen%20to%20have%20her%20husband%20elected%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20unopposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F13134452%2Fambedkar.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F13134452%2Fambedkar.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F13134452%2Fambedkar-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F13134452%2Fambedkar-1024x511.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F13134452%2Fambedkar-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-648335%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22599%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20with%20the%20women%20candidates%20of%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20Federation%20in%201942.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%20%E2%80%93%20CC0%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Patel%20wrote%20to%20Mavalankar%20on%20July%205%2C%201947%2C%20%E2%80%9CDr%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20nomination%20has%20been%20sent%20to%20PM.%20I%20hope%20there%20would%20be%20no%20contest%2C%20and%20he%20would%20be%20returned%20unopposed%20so%20that%20he%20could%20come%20here%20on%20the%2014th.%E2%80%9D%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20similarly%20wrote%20earlier%20on%20June%2030%2C%201947%2C%20to%20Kher%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20anxious%20that%20he%20should%20attend%20the%20next%20session%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20from%20the%2014th%20July%20and%20it%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20necessary%20that%20he%20should%20be%20elected%20immediately.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20after%20he%20became%20the%20law%20minister%2C%20Ambedkar%20was%20chosen%20as%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee%20formed%20to%20draft%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20As%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20he%20had%20to%20face%20criticism%20from%20several%20members%20of%20the%20Assembly%20whose%20views%20didn%E2%80%99t%20converge%20with%20that%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20but%20he%20handled%20the%20enormous%20task%20with%20great%20skill%2C%20tact%2C%20and%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20debates%2C%20he%20also%20delivered%20brilliant%20speeches.%20The%20following%20quote%20from%20his%20speech%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20on%20November%204%2C%201948%2C%20deserves%20special%20mention%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnother%20criticism%20against%20the%20Draft%20Constitution%20is%20that%20no%20part%20of%20it%20represents%20the%20ancient%20polity%20of%20India.%20It%20is%20said%20that%20the%20new%20Constitution%20should%20have%20been%20drafted%20on%20the%20ancient%20Hindu%20model%20of%20a%20State%20and%20that%20instead%20of%20incorporating%20Western%20theories%20the%20new%20Constitution%20should%20have%20been%20raised%20and%20built%20upon%20village%20panchayats%20and%20district%20panchayats%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%20I%20hold%20that%20these%20village%20republics%20have%20been%20the%20ruination%20of%20India.%20I%20am%2C%20therefore%2C%20surprised%20that%20those%20who%20condemn%20Provincialism%20and%20Communalism%20should%20come%20forward%20as%20champions%20of%20the%20village.%20What%20is%20the%20village%20but%20a%20sink%20of%20localism%2C%20a%20den%20of%20ignorance%2C%20narrow-mindedness%20and%20communalism%3F%20I%20am%20glad%20that%20the%20Draft%20Constitution%20has%20discarded%20the%20village%20and%20adopted%20the%20individual%20as%20a%20unit.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20speech%2C%20he%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CSome%20critics%20have%20taken%20objection%20to%20the%20description%20of%20India%20as%20a%20Union%20of%20States..%20some%20critics%20have%20said%20the%20Centre%20is%20too%20strong.%20Others%20have%20said%20that%20it%20must%20be%20made%20stronger.%20The%20Draft%20Constitution%20has%20struck%20a%20balance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20warned%20against%20the%20tendency%20to%20make%20the%20Centre%20stronger%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20cannot%20chew%20more%20than%20it%20can%20digest.%20Its%20strength%20must%20be%20commensurate%20with%20its%20weight.%20It%20would%20be%20a%20folly%20to%20make%20it%20so%20strong%20that%20it%20may%20fall%20by%20its%20own%20weight.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20day%20before%20the%20constitution%20was%20adopted%2C%20in%20his%20last%20speech%20to%20the%20Assembly%2C%20on%20November%2025%2C%201949%2C%20Ambedkar%20warned%20against%20the%20cult%20of%20Bhakti%20in%20politics.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20caution%20is%20far%20more%20necessary%20in%20the%20case%20of%20India%20than%20in%20the%20case%20of%20any%20other%20country.%20For%20in%20India%2C%20Bhakti%2C%20or%20what%20may%20be%20called%20the%20path%20of%20devotion%20or%20hero-worship%2C%20plays%20a%20part%20in%20its%20politics%2C%20unequalled%20in%20magnitude%20by%20the%20part%20it%20plays%20in%20the%20politics%20of%20any%20other%20country%20in%20the%20world.%20Bhakti%20in%20religion%20may%20be%20a%20road%20to%20the%20salvation%20of%20the%20soul.%20But%20in%20politics%2C%20Bhakti%20or%20hero-worship%20is%20a%20sure%20road%20to%20degradation%20and%20to%20eventual%20dictatorship.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20speech%2C%20he%20laid%20great%20emphasis%20on%20the%20principle%20of%20fraternity%20which%20%E2%80%9Cmeans%20a%20sense%20of%20common%20brotherhood%20of%20all%20Indians%E2%80%A6%20the%20principle%20which%20gives%20unity%20and%20solidarity%20to%20social%20life%E2%80%9D%20Ambedkar%20also%20explained%20why%20the%20realisation%20of%20the%20goal%20of%20nationhood%20for%20India%20is%20going%20to%20be%20difficult%20compared%20to%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fambedkar-jayanti-untouchability%5C%22%3EWhile%20Celebrating%20Ambedkar%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98National%20Hero%E2%80%99%2C%20We%20Must%20Not%20Forget%20His%20Central%20Thesis%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20United%20States%20has%20no%20caste%20problem.%20In%20India%2C%20there%20are%20castes.%20Castes%20are%20anti-national%2C%20in%20the%20first%20place%20because%20they%20bring%20about%20separation%20in%20social%20life.%20They%20are%20anti-national%20also%20because%20they%20generate%20jealousy%20and%20anty%20between%20caste%20and%20caste.%20But%20we%20must%20overcome%20all%20these%20difficulties%20if%20we%20wish%20to%20become%20a%20nation%20in%20reality.%20For%20fraternity%20can%20be%20a%20fact%20only%20when%20there%20is%20a%20nation.%20Without%20fraternity%2C%20equality%20and%20liberty%20will%20be%20no%20deeper%20than%20coats%20of%20paint.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20what%20stands%20out%20the%20most%20in%20this%20speech%20is%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20humility.%20He%20wanted%20no%20credit%20for%20himself%20but%20gave%20it%20to%20his%20colleagues.%20He%20said%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20credit%20that%20is%20given%20to%20me%20does%20not%20really%20belong%20to%20me.%20It%20belongs%20partly%20to%20Sir%20B.N.%20Rau%2C%20the%20Constitutional%20Adviser%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20who%20prepared%20a%20rough%20draft%20of%20the%20Constitution%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20Drafting%20Committee%E2%80%A6.%20Much%20greater%20share%20of%20the%20credit%20must%20go%20to%20Mr.%20S.N.%20Mukherjee%2C%20the%20Chief%20Draftsman%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20His%20ability%20to%20put%20the%20most%20intricate%20proposals%20in%20the%20simplest%20and%20clearest%20legal%20form%20can%20rarely%20be%20equalled%E2%80%A6.I%20must%20not%20omit%20to%20mention%20the%20members%20of%20the%20staff%20working%20under%20Mr.%20Mukherjee.%20For%20I%20know%20how%20hard%20they%20worked%20and%20how%20long%20they%20have%20toiled%2C%20sometimes%20even%20beyond%20midnight.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20may%20have%20denied%20himself%20the%20credit%2C%20but%20many%20knew%20the%20reality.%20Rajendra%20Prasad%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20stated%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20realised%2C%20as%20nobody%20else%20could%20have%2C%20with%20what%20zeal%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Drafting%20Committee%20and%20especially%20its%20Chairman%2C%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20his%20indifferent%20health%2C%20have%20worked.%20We%20could%20never%20make%20a%20decision%20which%20was%2C%20or%20could%20ever%20be%2C%20so%20right%20as%20when%20we%20put%20him%20on%20the%20Drafting%20Committee%20and%20made%20him%20its%20Chairman.%20He%20has%20not%20only%20justified%20his%20selection%20but%20has%20added%20lustre%20to%20the%20work%20which%20he%20has%20done.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmbedkar%20at%20the%20end%20of%20his%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindu%20Code%20Bill%20was%20the%20first%20revolutionary%20step%20towards%20women%E2%80%99s%20empowerment%20in%20the%20Nehru%20era%2C%20but%20its%20passage%20in%20parliament%20met%20with%20several%20roadblocks%20despite%20both%20prime%20minister%20Nehru%20and%20law%20minister%20Ambedkar%20were%20deeply%20committed%20to%20it.%20It%20was%20ultimately%20passed%2C%20but%20not%20before%20Baba%20Saheb%20resigned%20from%20the%20Cabinet%20frustrated%20by%20its%20delay.%20Savita%20Ambedkar%20writes%20in%20her%20book%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPrime%20Minister%20Nehru%20had%20just%20returned%20from%20a%20tour%20of%20America%20when%20Saheb%20met%20him%20and%20got%20from%20him%20the%20approval%20to%20table%20the%20bill.%20Nehru%20assured%20Saheb%20that%20he%20would%20get%20the%20bill%20approved%E2%80%A6but%20Speaker%20Mavalankar%2C%20President%20Dr.%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20and%20Home%20Minister%20Vallabhbhai%20Patel%20were%20openly%20against%20it%E2%80%A6%20It%20was%20under%20these%20difficult%20circumstances%20that%20Doctor%20Saheb%20tabled%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%205%20Feb%201951.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20the%20best%20efforts%20of%20Nehru%2C%20the%20Bill%20could%20not%20be%20passed%20till%20the%20end%20of%20September%201951%20and%20Ambedkar%20submitted%20his%20resignation%20from%20the%20Cabinet%20on%20September%2027%2C%201951.%20The%20Hindu%20Code%20Bill%20was%20ultimately%20passed%20after%20the%20general%20elections%20in%201952%20by%20breaking%20it%20into%20various%20sections%20which%20took%20almost%20the%20entire%20period%20of%20the%20first%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20from%20Bombay%20State%20(now%2C%20Maharashtra)%20in%20April%201952.%20But%20his%20health%20started%20failing%20following%20a%20heart%20attack%20in%20November%201953%20while%20on%20a%20train%20journey%20from%20Delhi%20to%20Bombay.%20Though%20he%20continued%20to%20remain%20active%20in%20public%20life%20(for%20instance%20in%201954%20he%20addressed%20the%20Defence%20Services%20College%2C%20Willington)%2C%20he%20started%20taking%20more%20interest%20in%20religious%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20decade%20earlier%20Nehru%20had%20written%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Discovery%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20his%20attraction%20to%20Buddhism%20for%20its%20fight%20against%20priestcraft%20and%20ritualism%20as%20well%20as%20for%20its%20ethical%20approach%20to%20life.%20But%20Ambedkar%20had%20one%20more%20reason%20for%20his%20preference%20for%20Buddhism%3A%20the%20religion%20had%20no%20caste.%20He%20wrote%20a%20book%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Buddha%20and%20His%20Gospel%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20title%20of%20which%20was%20later%20changed%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Buddha%20and%20His%20Dhamma%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20lost%20interest%20in%20politics%20in%20the%20evening%20of%20his%20life%2C%20and%20in%20a%20state%20of%20rapidly%20deteriorating%20health%2C%20Baba%20Saheb%20began%20preparations%20for%20converting%20to%20Buddhism.%20It%20was%20on%20October%2014%2C%201956%2C%20less%20than%20two%20months%20before%20his%20death%2C%20that%20a%20%3Cem%3EDeeksha%3C%2Fem%3E%20ceremony%20was%20held%20at%20Nagpur%2C%20the%20venue%20preferred%20to%20Mumbai%20after%20great%20deliberation%20and%20debate%20between%20the%20Ambedkarites%20of%20both%20the%20cities.%20Nearly%20six%20lakh%20followers%20of%20Ambedkar%20embraced%20Buddhism%20with%20their%20leader%2C%20who%20had%20vowed%20way%20back%20in%201935%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20born%20a%20Hindu%2C%20but%20I%20shall%20not%20die%20a%20Hindu.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaba%20Saheb%20passed%20away%20peacefully%20in%20his%20sleep%20before%20dawn%20on%20December%206%20in%20Delhi.%20Amongst%20the%20early%20visitors%20to%20his%20residence%20to%20pay%20their%20condolences%20at%20Alipore%20Road%20(now%20a%20memorial)%20were%20Nehru%20and%20many%20Union%20ministers%2C%20including%20Babu%20Jagjivan%20Ram%2C%20who%20made%20arrangements%20for%20the%20mortal%20remains%20of%20Ambedkar%20to%20be%20carried%20to%20Mumbai.%20Savita%20Ambedkar%20recorded%20for%20posterity%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20Saheb%E2%80%99s%20passing%20away%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20offered%20me%20a%20job%20of%20a%20medical%20officer%20in%20a%20government%20hospital.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20even%20showed%20readiness%20to%20take%20me%20into%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20but%20I%20turned%20down%20the%20offers.%20The%20reason%20was%20that%20Doctor%20Saheb%20had%20made%20me%20give%20up%20my%20job%20after%20marriage%2C%20and%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20think%20it%20proper%20to%20go%20against%20his%20wishes%E2%80%A6.Later%20President%20Sarvepalli%20Radhakrishnan%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20also%20showed%20readiness%20to%20get%20me%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20but%20I%20humbly%20declined.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESavita%20Ambedkar%20died%20in%202003%20living%20up%20to%20her%20vow%20she%20had%20taken%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20live%20as%20an%20Ambedkar%2C%20and%20I%20shall%20die%20an%20Ambedkar.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPraveen%20Davar%20is%C2%A0an%20ex-Army%20officer%2C%20a%20columnist%2C%20and%20the%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20Freedom%20Struggle%20and%20Beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701868256000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F07092014%2FDr._Babasaheb_Ambedkar_delivering_a_speech_2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Freacknowledging-role-ambedkar-architect-india-constitution%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Though%20he%20lived%20only%20nine%20years%20after%20Independence%2C%20he%20left%20an%20indelible%20mark%20on%20the%20history%20of%20modern%20India%2C%20which%20possibly%20is%20greater%20than%20his%20contribution%20during%20the%20freedom%20struggle.%20He%20died%20on%20December%206%2C%201956.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Freacknowledging-role-ambedkar-architect-india-constitution%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22a