r%20Than%20Exclusive%20Electoral%20Concerns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04213108%2FWide-voting-photo.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20results%20of%20the%20four%20assembly%20elections%20might%20come%20as%20a%20disappointment%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20big%20takeaway%20is%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20distinct%20Telangana%20model%20of%20social%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20depicted%20to%20be%20a%20distant%20third%20behind%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20and%20BJP.%20It%20began%20to%20pick%20up%20momentum%20soon%20after%20its%20victory%20in%20Karnataka.%20It%20began%20with%20a%20hope%20that%20started%20to%20fructify%20into%20a%20palpably%20favourable%20perception%20among%20the%20people%20of%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDefeating%20the%20BRS%20is%20no%20easy%20feat%2C%20given%20its%20track%20record%20of%20dispersing%20welfare%20policies%20such%20as%20Rythu%20Bandhu%2C%20Kalyana%20Laxmi%2C%20Shaadi%20Mubarak%20and%20pensions%20for%20the%20old%2C%20and%20providing%20water%20for%20both%20drinking%20and%20irrigation%20purposes%20through%20Mission%20Bhagiratha%20and%20Mission%20Kakatiya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20minister%20K.%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20(KCR)%20government%20faltered%20on%20the%20front%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Funemployed-resentment-against-mlas-down-brs%2Farticleshow%2F105711389.cms%5C%22%3Eproviding%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20by%20undermining%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Ftelangana-education-sector-2023-budget%5C%22%3Efunding%20for%20education%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20was%20palpable%20discontent%20among%20the%20youth.%20The%20Congress%20had%20no%20effective%20alternative%20%E2%80%93%20until%20it%20formulated%20its%20six-point%20programme%2C%20very%20similar%20to%20the%20way%20it%20did%20in%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20was%20the%20visible%20effect%20of%20a%20much%20deeper%20churning%20that%20took%20place.%20This%20deeper%20process%20could%20take%20on%20not%20only%20the%20welfarism%20of%20the%20BRS%20but%20also%20the%20unbridled%20money%20power%20that%20both%20the%20BRS%20and%20BJP%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20Congress%20won%20despite%20the%20change%20in%20strategy%20by%20the%20BJP%20to%20have%20consciously%20receded%20to%20the%20background%20to%20give%20the%20BRS%20the%20edge%20it%20required.%20The%20change%20in%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20began%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Funion-minister-kishan-reddy-made-telangana-bjp-chief-punjab-jharkhand-get-new-presidents%5C%22%3Eremoval%20of%20Bandi%20Sanjay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20firebrand%20OBC%20leader%20who%20has%20to%20be%20credited%20with%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20growing%20footprint%20in%20Telangana.%20The%20voters%20seem%20to%20have%20rejected%20this%20strategy%20of%20being%20taken%20on%20a%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04210856%2FBandi-Sanjay-1024x683.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04210856%2FBandi-Sanjay-1024x683.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04210856%2FBandi-Sanjay-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04210856%2FBandi-Sanjay.jpg%201080w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687695%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20BJP%20rose%20to%20being%20the%20primary%20opposition%20party%20in%20Telangana%20under%20Bandi%20Sanjay%E2%80%99s%20leadership%2C%20but%20he%20was%20reassigned%20in%20July%20this%20year.%C2%A0Photo%3A%20X%2F%40bandisanjay_bjp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20popular%20perception%20that%20settled%20in%20was%20that%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20BRS%20and%20the%20All%20India%20Majlis-e-Ittehadul%20Muslimeen%20(AIMIM)%20were%20fighting%20the%20election%20together%2C%20making%20it%20a%20bi-polar%20contest%2C%20as%20against%20a%20multipolar%20one%2C%20which%20is%20how%20the%20BJP%20expected%20to%20project%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuslims%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20rejecting%20AIMIM%20leader%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20outside%20of%20Hyderabad%20city.%20They%20did%20not%20fall%20for%20the%20bait%20of%20Owaisi%20being%20projected%20as%20the%20sole%20Muslim%20representative%20when%20the%20community%20was%20being%20pushed%20onto%20the%20back%20foot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuslim%20voters%20need%20to%20be%20credited%20for%20seeing%20through%20this%20strategy%20even%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3B%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20somewhat%20dubious%20role%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20played%20in%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20riots%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20none%20of%20the%20so-called%20secular%20parties%20stood%20by%20them%2C%20they%20overwhelmingly%20voted%20for%20these%20parties%20rejecting%2C%20Owaisi%E2%80%99s%20overtures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20mostly%20the%20educated%20and%20upper-caste%20youth%20among%20Muslims%20that%20was%20aspirational%20and%20saw%20fulfilment%20in%20gaining%20exclusive%20Muslim%20representation%2C%20but%20the%20common%20Muslim%20on%20the%20street%20rejected%20this%20simple-minded%20representational%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGaining%20representation%20is%20significant%20in%20any%20democracy%20but%20not%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20social%20development.%20Pitching%20one%20against%20the%20other%20is%20how%20majoritarian-caste%20and%20religious-hegemony%20is%20maintained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20also%20distinct%20about%20the%20electoral%20outcome%20in%20Telangana%20was%20that%20the%20Dalits%20and%20the%20OBCs%20too%20did%20not%20stop%20at%20empty-minded%20representation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20in%20much%20of%20North%20India%2C%20the%20BJP%20began%20to%20woo%20the%20sub-castes%20within%20the%20Dalits%20and%20the%20dominant%20castes%20among%20the%20OBCs.%20It%20promised%20to%20appoint%20an%20OBC%20chief%20minister%20and%20followed%20it%20up%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fahead-of-telangana-polls-pm-modi-sets-in-motion-madiga-sub-categorisation-process-report%5C%22%3Eagreeing%20to%20an%20appeal%20by%20Krishna%20Madiga%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20an%20independent%20Dalit%20group%20called%20the%20Madiga%20Reservation%20Porata%20Samithi%20(MRPS)%2C%20for%20sub-categorisation%20in%20reservations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16141604%2FThe-Wire-82-1024x478.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16141604%2FThe-Wire-82-1024x478.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16141604%2FThe-Wire-82-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16141604%2FThe-Wire-82.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685050%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22392%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20with%20Manda%20Krishna%20Madiga%20of%20MRPS%20in%20Hyderabad%20on%20November%2011.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FNarendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20height%20of%20the%20campaign%2C%20Krishna%20Madiga%20shared%20the%20dais%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20who%20gave%20a%20call%20to%20work%20under%20the%20Madiga%20leader%20to%20fight%20for%20the%20sub-division%20of%20reservations%20for%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes.%20On%20hearing%20this%2C%20Krishna%20Madiga%20broke%20down%20and%20was%20embraced%20by%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20powerful%20script%20with%20tremendous%20mobilisational%20power.%20But%20again%2C%20this%20did%20not%20work%20in%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20favour%2C%20as%20Dalits%20seem%20to%20have%20overwhelmingly%20voted%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%20and%20OBCs%20too%20did%20not%20stop%20at%20the%20question%20of%20representation.%20Again%2C%20it%20was%20a%20tiny%20section%20of%20what%20I%20refer%20to%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fhow-indias-new-mezzanine-elite-classes-enable-majoritarian-politics%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98mezzanine%20elites%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20comprising%20educated%20youth%20and%20the%20employed%20middle%20class%20that%20was%20impressed%20with%20the%20representation%20being%20promised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20spectacle%20could%20have%2C%20perhaps%2C%20swept%20away%20the%20Dalit-Bahujans%20in%20the%20North.%20The%20outcome%20in%20Telangana%20reflects%20a%20new%20and%20emergent%20faultline%20between%20the%20Dalit-Bahujans%2C%20who%20get%20mobilised%20around%20Ambedkarite%20rhetoric%20but%20are%20essentially%20confined%20to%20identitarianism%2C%20and%20the%20bulk%20of%20common%20voters%20who%20are%20prepared%20to%20look%20beyond%20and%20realise%20the%20need%20for%20greater%20solidarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20also%20is%20the%20intriguing%20case%20with%20the%20Muslims%2C%20where%20it%20is%20the%20middle%20class%20and%20urban%20Muslims%20who%20hanker%20behind%20an%20exclusive%20Muslim%20identity%20and%20campaigns%20centred%20on%20Islamophobia%20and%20Hindu-Muslim%20rhetoric%20run%20by%20the%20AIMIM%20and%20by%20Akbaruddin%20Owaisi%20in%20particular%2C%20while%20the%20common%20Muslim%20on%20the%20street%20is%20willing%20to%20go%20beyond%20the%20logic%20of%20polarisation%20and%20empty%20representation%20to%20lay%20a%20greater%20premium%20on%20welfare%20and%20cross-religious%20solidarities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20distinct%20aspect%20of%20the%20Telangana%20model%20of%20social%20development%20is%20that%20electoral%20outcomes%20are%20driven%20by%20a%20social%20agenda%20rather%20than%20exclusive%20political%20or%20electoral%20calculations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelangana%20is%20called%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98udyamala%20gadda%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(land%20of%20protest%20movements)%20and%20the%20demand%20for%20a%20separate%20state%20was%20driven%20by%20the%20ideal%20of%20a%20social%20democratic%20Telangana%20reflected%20in%20its%20slogan%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Esamajika%3C%2Fem%3E%20Telangana%E2%80%99.%20The%20Telangana%20movement%20was%20not%20characterised%20by%20an%20exclusive%20regional%20sentiment%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20for%20social%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20on%20this%20front%20that%20the%20BRS%20fell%20awfully%20short.%20The%20arrogance%20of%20BRS%20leader%20KCR%20became%20a%20sore%20point%2C%20reminding%20the%20people%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Edorala%3C%2Fem%3E%20Telangana%E2%80%99%20(Telangana%20of%20the%20feudal%20landlords).%20The%20BRS%20stands%20rejected%20due%20to%20a%20sentiment%20of%20self-respect%20moving%20beyond%20high-handedness.%20Even%20if%20the%20BRS%20implemented%20welfare%20policies%2C%20its%20handling%20of%20day-to-day%20affairs%20was%20seen%20as%20objectionable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-bharat-rashtra-samithi-congress-kcr%5C%22%3EIn%20Telangana%2C%20Five%20Trends%20Highlight%20Divides%2C%20Gains%2C%20Losses%20and%20Blows%20to%20Expansion%20Plans%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBalladeer%20Gaddar%20had%20famously%20referred%20to%20this%20as%20landlords%20moving%20from%20their%20%3Cem%3Egadis%3C%2Fem%3E%20(forts)%20to%20farmhouses.%20It%20is%20such%20a%20sentiment%20that%20made%20cross-caste%20solidarities%20feasible%20and%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20election%2C%20there%20was%20an%20experiment%20here%20similar%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkarnataka%2Feddelu-karnataka-to-hold-felicitation-event%2Farticle66886175.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eeddelu%3C%2Fem%3E%20Karnataka%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20(wake%20up%20Karnataka)%20civil%20society%20collective%20in%20the%20neighbouring%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndependent%20social%20organisations%20working%20on%20the%20ground%20around%20a%20number%20of%20issues%20such%20as%20employment%2C%20education%2C%20women%E2%80%99s%20issues%2C%20land%2C%20famine%2C%20water%20resources%2C%20child%20labour%2C%20health%20and%20caste%2C%20among%20others%2C%20came%20together%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Ftelangana%2F2023%2Fsep%2F02%2Ftelangana-peoples-joint-action-committee-to-fight-for-public-issues-2610960.html%5C%22%3ETelangana%20People%E2%80%99s%20Joint%20Action%20Committee%3C%2Fa%3E%20(TPJAC).%20The%20social%20activists%20campaigned%20on%20the%20ground%20to%20vote%20against%20the%20BRS%2C%20but%20not%20directly%20for%20Congress.%20They%20highlighted%20social%20issues%20of%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClose%20to%20the%20polling%20date%2C%20the%20projected%20chief%20ministerial%20candidate%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20Revanth%20Reddy%2C%20held%20a%20two-hour%20live%20discussion%20with%20professor%20Haragopal%2C%20president%20of%20the%20TPJAC%3B%20M.%20Kodandaram%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Telangana%20Jana%20Samithi%3B%20and%20Ramachandra%20Murthy%2C%20an%20independent%20senior%20journalist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F22083857%2FA.-Revanth-Reddy-300x200.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F22083857%2FA.-Revanth-Reddy-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F22083857%2FA.-Revanth-Reddy.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-553493%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETelangana%20state%20Congress%20chief%20and%20the%20projected%20new%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20state%2C%20Revanth%20Reddy.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FA.%20Revanth%20Reddy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20of%20them%20questioned%20the%20policy%20framework%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20elicited%20a%20promise%20that%20the%20Congress%20would%20not%20indulge%20in%20high-handedness%20%E2%80%93%20otherwise%2C%20the%20social%20activists%20warned%20Reddy%20that%20they%20would%20hit%20the%20streets%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20did%20we%20last%20see%20such%20social%20activism%20have%20such%20an%20impact%20on%20political%20leaders%3F%20This%20continues%20to%20remain%20the%20core%20of%20the%20Telangana%20model%20of%20social%20development%20that%20goes%20beyond%20electoral%20representation.%20There%20is%20a%20direct%20synergy%20between%20civil%20society%20and%20social%20activism%20that%20can%20potentially%20influence%20public%20opinion%20and%20electoral%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20to%20counter%20both%20the%20kinds%20of%20consensus%20that%20seem%20to%20occupy%20the%20political%20horizon%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20one%20the%20Congress-initiated%20neoliberal%20consensus%20since%20the%201990s%20and%20the%20other%20the%20BJP-initiated%20cultural%20nationalist%20consensus%20since%202002%2C%20the%20only%20way%20forward%20seems%20to%20be%20to%20create%20this%20kind%20of%20resurgent%20space%20for%20social%20mobilisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Congress%20and%20other%20parties%20are%20to%20revive%2C%20they%20could%20possibly%20look%20to%20the%20Telangana%20model%20of%20social%20development.%20This%2C%20of%20course%2C%20for%20the%20moment%20is%20limited%20to%20the%20South%20and%20parts%20of%20the%20East%2C%20such%20as%20Bengal.%20There%20is%20no%20traction%20for%20such%20a%20model%20in%20the%20North%2C%20as%20there%20is%20no%20presence%20of%20independent%20social%20mobilisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20clues%20one%20could%20draw%20for%20the%20North%20from%20the%20Telangana%20model%20of%20social%20development%20could%20well%20be%20relevant%20in%20days%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fajay-gudavarthy%5C%22%3EAjay%20Gudavarthy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Political%20Studies%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701864866000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F04213108%2FWide-voting-photo.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-model-of-development%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20core%20feature%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Telangana%20model%E2%80%99%20of%20social%20development%20that%20goes%20beyond%20electoral%20representation%20is%20a%20direct%20synergy%20between%20civil%20society%20and%20social%20activism%20that%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20influence%20public%20opinion%20and%20electoral%20outcomes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-model-of-development%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shree%20Cement%20plans%20to%20bid%20for%20lithium%20mining%20rights%20in%20Jammu-Kashmir%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701864778000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-02%2F16%2Ffull%2F1676562940-08.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fshree-c