Mr.%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnHon%E2%80%99ble%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnSupreme%20Court%20of%20India%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnNew%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDear%20Sir%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20deeply%20anguished%20at%20certain%20happenings%20about%20the%20listing%20of%20cases%20by%20the%20Registry%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20and%20hence%20I%20am%20constrained%20to%20address%20this%20open%20letter%20to%20you%20as%20the%20Master%20of%20the%20Roster%20on%20your%20administrative%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20124%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20provides%20that%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20shall%20be%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20consisting%20of%20a%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20and%2C%20until%20Parliament%20by%20law%20prescribes%20a%20larger%20number%2C%20of%20not%20more%20than%20%5Bseven%5D%20other%20Judges.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20administrative%20control%20over%20the%20court%2C%20but%20on%20the%20judicial%20side%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eyou%20are%20the%20first%20among%20the%20equals%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%20As%20Master%20of%20the%20Roster%20you%20alone%20have%20the%20prerogative%20to%20constitute%20bench%20and%20allocate%20cases%20to%20the%20benches%20so%20constituted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Article%20145%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20given%20powers%20to%20make%20rules%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20regulating%20generally%20the%20practice%20and%20procedure%20of%20the%20Court%20subject%20to%20approval%20of%20the%20President%E2%80%9D%2C%20including%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CRules%20as%20to%20the%20procedure%20for%20hearing%20appeals%20and%20other%20matters%20pertaining%20to%20appeals%20including%20the%20time%20within%20which%20appeals%20to%20the%20Court%20are%20to%20be%20entered%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3ESupreme%20Court%20Rules%2C%202013%20have%20been%20framed%2C%20which%20inter%20alia%20provide%20in%20Order%203%20Rule%202%20as%20under%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%20may%20assign%2C%20and%20the%20Secretary%20General%2C%20may%2C%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20delegate%2C%20to%20an%20Additional%20Registrar%2C%20Deputy%20Registrar%20or%20Assistant%20Registrar%2C%20any%20function%20required%20by%20these%20rules%20to%20be%20exercised%20by%20the%20Registrar.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERules%20of%202013%20are%20silent%20as%20to%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20Master%20of%20the%20Roster%20to%20constitute%20roster%2C%20constituting%20Benches%20and%20for%20allocation%20of%20the%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Handbook%20on%20Practice%20and%20Procedure%20of%20the%20Court%20and%20Office%20Procedure%20on%20Judicial%20side%20published%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20in%202017%2C%20however%2C%20provides%20in%20Chapter%20VI%20Para%201%20as%20under%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20roster%20shall%20be%20prepared%20by%20the%20Registrar%20(J-I)%20under%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice.%20It%20may%20contain%20general%20or%20special%20instructions%20regarding%20assignment%2Fallocation%20of%20work%20to%20a%20Bench%20and%20includes%20allocation%20of%20work%20of%20a%20Bench%2C%20on%20account%20of%20non-availability%2C%20to%20another%20Bench.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPara%202%20deals%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fsca_esv%3D587921074%26rlz%3D1C1VDKB_enIN1043IN1043%26sxsrf%3DAM9HkKnocQVoaw94GxjhR_qBrgM92T7RMg%3A1701754528050%26q%3Dcontingencies%26spell%3D1%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D2ahUKEwigmo7RyfeCAxXGqFYBHfJAAtoQBSgAegQICBAC%5C%22%3Econtingencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20provides%20as%20under%3A%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20order%20to%20meet%20contingencies%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20may%2C%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20direct%20the%20Registrar%20(J-I)%20to%20prepare%20roster%20instructions%20or%20amendments%20for%20re-allocation%20of%20judicial%20work.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20Roster%20once%20prepared%20under%20your%20direction%20must%20guide%20the%20assignment%2Fallocation%20of%20work%20to%20a%20Bench%20including%20the%20allocation%20of%20work%20of%20a%20Bench%20on%20account%20of%20non-availability%2C%20to%20another%20Bench%20is%20final.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChapter%20XIII%20deals%20with%20the%20listing%20of%20cases%20and%20commands%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EThe%20Registrar%20(J-I)%20shall%20list%20the%20cases%20before%20the%20Benches%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20roster%20under%20the%20directions%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20dealing%20with%20%E2%80%9CCases%2C%20Coram%20%26amp%3B%20Listing%E2%80%9D%20provides%20in%20Para%202%20as%20under%3A%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CFresh%20cases%20are%20allocated%20as%20per%20subject%20category%20through%20automatic%20computer%20allocation%2C%20unless%20coram%20is%20given%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20or%20the%20Filing%20Counter%3A%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPara%203%20provides%20that%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20coram%20of%20the%20Bench%20where%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3Ea%20main%20case%20has%20been%20listed%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3Enotice%20has%20been%20issued%20till%20grant%20of%20special%20leave%20to%20appeal%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3Ea%20case%20has%20been%20dismissed%2C%20allowed%20or%20disposed%20of%3B%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3Ea%20case%20has%20been%20heard%20in-part%20at%20admission%20hearing%20stage.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3Eshall%20be%20updated%20in%20the%20computer%20for%20future%20listing%20of%20admission%20hearing%20cases%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPara%206%20specifically%20says%3A%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20first%20coram%20is%20not%20available%20on%20a%20particular%20day%20on%20account%20of%20retirement%2C%20the%20case%20shall%20be%20listed%20before%20the%20Judge%20constituting%20the%20second%20coram.%20If%20second%20coram%20is%20also%20not%20available%2C%20the%20case%20shall%20not%20be%20listed%20on%20that%20day.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20position%20is%20amplified%20in%20Para%2010%20%26amp%3B%2011.%20Thus%2C%20once%20the%20case%20has%20been%20listed%20or%20notice%20has%20been%20issued%20or%20has%20been%20dismissed%20or%20disposed%20of%20or%20has%20been%20heard%20in%20part%20at%20admission%20hearing%20stage%20the%20case%20thereafter%20can%20only%20be%20listed%20before%20the%20bench%20of%20first%20coram%20and%20none%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPara%2047%20deals%20with%20criminal%20matter%20and%20provide%20as%20under%3A%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20criminal%20cases%2C%20except%20writ%20petition%20(criminal)%20but%20excluding%20habeas%20corpus%20petitions%2C%20where%20service%20is%20complete%20but%20affidavit%20in%20opposition%20has%20not%20been%20filed%2C%20shall%20be%20listed%20before%20the%20regular%20Bench%20having%20the%20coram%20in%20the%20case%20and%20not%20under%20incomplete%20category%20before%20the%20Court%20of%20Registrar.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20that%20this%20sound%20practice%20is%20followed%3B%20if%20any%20direction%20is%20given%20about%20listing%20of%20any%20case%20by%20a%20superior%20orally%2C%20the%20concerned%20official%20must%20seek%20written%20confirmation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotes%20under%20the%20Section%20provide%20as%20under%3A%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CSave%20in%20case%20of%20a%20single%20coram%2C%20wherever%20a%20main%20case%20or%20application%20could%20not%20be%20listed%20before%20the%20first%20coram%2C%20it%20shall%20be%20listed%20before%20the%20second%20and%20then%20third%20coram%2C%20wherever%20applicable%2C%20and%2C%20if%20available%2C%20in%20seniority%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%202%20gives%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20the%20power%20to%20list%20the%20case%20in%20case%20of%20non-availability%20of%20single%20coram%20or%20members%20of%20the%20bench%20on%20account%20of%20retirement%20or%20otherwise.%20If%20not%20listed%20through%20computer%20allocation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%203%20however%20gives%20the%20following%20power%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice.%20This%20is%20an%20extraordinary%20power%20to%20upset%20the%20roster%20and%20to%20%E2%80%9Cpick%20and%20choose%E2%80%9D%20and%20allocate%20and%20assign%20any%20appeal%20or%20cause%20or%20matter%20to%20any%20judge%20or%20judges%20of%20the%20Court.%20However%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20can%20only%20exercise%20the%20power%20as%20per%20the%20practice%20and%20in%20case%20the%20coram%20as%20per%20roster%20is%20available%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20cannot%20exercise%20power%20to%20take%20away%20any%20case%20before%20the%20available%20coram%20and%20place%20it%20before%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20no%20doubt%20that%20as%20Master%20of%20Roster%2C%20you%20have%20not%20exercised%20power%20under%20Note%203%20referred%20above%20as%20no%20information%20is%20available%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Court%20has%20in%20this%20regard%20held%20that%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EIn%20his%20capacity%20as%20a%20Judge%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20is%20primus%20inter%20pares%3A%20the%20first%20among%20equals.%20In%20the%20discharge%20of%20his%20other%20functions%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20occupies%20a%20position%20which%20is%20sui%20generis.%20Article%20124(1)%20postulates%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20shall%20consist%20of%20a%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20and%20other%20Judges.%20Article%20146%20%5B%20%E2%80%9C146.%20Officers%20and%20servants%20and%20the%20expenses%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%E2%80%94(1)%20Appointments%20of%20officers%20and%20servants%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20shall%20be%20made%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20or%20such%20other%20Judge%20or%20officer%20of%20the%20Court%20as%20he%20may%20direct%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EProvided%20that%20the%20President%20may%20by%20rule%20require%20that%20in%20such%20cases%20as%20may%20be%20specified%20in%20the%20rule%2C%20no%20person%20not%20already%20attached%20to%20the%20Court%20shall%20be%20appointed%20to%20any%20office%20connected%20with%20the%20Court%2C%20save%20after%20consultation%20with%20the%20Union%20Public%20Service%20Commission.(2)%20Subject%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20any%20law%20made%20by%20Parliament%2C%20the%20conditions%20of%20service%20of%20officers%20and%20servants%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20shall%20be%20such%20as%20may%20be%20prescribed%20by%20rules%20made%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20or%20by%20some%20other%20Judge%20or%20officer%20of%20the%20Court%20authorised%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20to%20make%20rules%20for%20the%20purpose%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EProvided%20that%20the%20rules%20made%20under%20this%20clause%20shall%2C%20so%20far%20as%20they%20relate%20to%20salaries%2C%20allowances%20leave%20or%20pensions%2C%20require%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20President.(3)%20The%20administrative%20expenses%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20including%20all%20salaries%2C%20allowances%20and%20pensions%20payable%20to%20or%20in%20respect%20of%20the%20officers%20and%20servants%20of%20the%20Court%2C%20shall%20be%20charged%20upon%20the%20Consolidated%20Fund%20of%20India%2C%20and%20any%20fees%20or%20other%20moneys%20taken%20by%20the%20Court%20shall%20form%20part%20of%20that%20Fund.%E2%80%9D%5D%20reaffirms%20the%20position%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20as%20the%20head%20of%20the%20institution.%20From%20an%20institutional%20perspective%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20is%20placed%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20In%20the%20allocation%20of%20cases%20and%20the%20constitution%20of%20Benches%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20has%20an%20exclusive%20prerogative.%20As%20a%20repository%20of%20constitutional%20trust%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20is%20an%20institution%20in%20himself.%20The%20authority%20which%20is%20conferred%20upon%20the%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20it%20must%20be%20remembered%2C%20is%20vested%20in%20a%20high%20constitutional%20functionary.%20The%20authority%20is%20entrusted%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20because%20such%20an%20entrustment%20of%20functions%20is%20necessary%20for%20the%20efficient%20transaction%20of%20the%20administrative%20and%20judicial%20work%20of%20the%20Court.%20The%20ultimate%20purpose%20behind%20the%20entrustment%20of%20authority%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20able%20to%20fulfil%20and%20discharge%20the%20constitutional%20obligations%20which%20govern%20and%20provide%20the%20rationale%20for%20its%20existence.%20The%20entrustment%20of%20functions%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20as%20the%20head%20of%20the%20institution%2C%20is%20with%20the%20purpose%20of%20securing%20the%20position%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20an%20independent%20safeguard%20for%20the%20preservation%20of%20personal%20liberty.%20There%20cannot%20be%20a%20presumption%20of%20mistrust.%20The%20oath%20of%20office%20demands%20nothing%20less.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20I%20have%20personally%20come%20across%20a%20number%20of%20cases%20listed%20before%20various%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Benches%20upon%20first%20listing%20and%2F%20or%20in%20which%20notice%20have%20been%20issued%2C%20being%20taken%20away%20from%20those%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Benches%20and%20listed%20before%20other%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Benches.%20Despite%20first%20coram%20being%20available%20the%20matters%20are%20being%20listed%20before%20a%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Benches%20in%20which%20second%20coram%20presides.%20Matters%20listed%20before%20Court%20No.%202%2C%204%2C%206%2C%207%20amongst%20others%20have%20been%20shifted%20out%20and%20listed%20before%20other%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Benches%20in%20clear%20disregard%20of%20the%20Rules%2C%20the%20Handbook%20on%20Practice%20and%20Office%20Procedure%20referred%20above%20and%20established%20Practice%20and%20Convention.%20Curiously%2C%20the%20Seniority%20of%20the%20first%20coram%20is%20also%20being%20ignored%20in%20doing%20so.%20Our%20attention%20is%20also%20been%20drawn%20by%20esteemed%20Colleagues%20at%20the%20Bar%2C%20Seniors%2C%20and%20Advocates%20on%20Record%20(AoRs)%2C%20about%20various%20cases%20in%20which%20they%20have%20appeared%20in%20the%20first%20instance%20on%20numerous%20occasions%2C%20later%20the%20matters%20being%20listed%20before%20different%20Benches.%20It%20would%20not%20be%20proper%20for%20me%20to%20enumerate%20these%20matters%20as%20many%20of%20them%20are%20pending.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20would%20not%20be%20out%20of%20place%20to%20mention%20that%20these%20matters%20include%20some%20sensitive%20matters%20involving%20human%20rights%2C%20Freedom%20of%20Speech%2C%20Democracy%2C%20and%20Functioning%20of%20Statutory%20and%20Constitutional%20Institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20your%20appointment%2C%20strong%20hopes%20were%20created%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20Citizens%20that%20under%20your%20Leadership%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20will%20rise%20to%20greater%20heights%2C%20the%20march%20towards%20which%20has%20somehow%20paused%20for%20some%20time%20earlier.%20The%20scars%20caused%20on%20account%20of%20such%20improprieties%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%20on%20justice%20delivery%20have%20not%20healed%20as%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESir%2C%20I%20personally%20hold%20you%20in%20high%20esteem%20and%20You%20and%20your%20Colleagues%20and%20all%20those%20associated%20with%20Administration%20of%20Justice%20in%20the%20Country%20are%20aware%20that%20that%20I%20have%20highest%20respect%20and%20love%20for%20Judiciary.%20But%20I%20will%20be%20failing%20in%20my%20duty%20imposed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20itself%20when%20it%20held%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ethe%20lawyers%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20fearless%20and%20independent%20in%20the%20protection%20of%20rights%20of%20litigants%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3EAnd%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20lawyers%20are%20supposed%20to%20protect%2C%20is%20the%20legal%20system%20and%20procedure%20of%20law%20of%20deciding%20the%20cases.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20held%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EIndependent%20Bar%20and%20independent%20Bench%20form%20the%20backbone%20of%20Democracy.%20In%20order%20to%20preserve%20the%20very%20independence%2C%20the%20observance%20of%20constitutional%20values%2C%20mutual%20reverence%20and%20self-respect%20are%20absolutely%20necessary.%20The%20Bar%20and%20Bench%20are%20complimentary%20to%20each%20other.%20Without%20active%20cooperation%20of%20the%20Bar%20and%20the%20Bench%2C%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20preserve%20the%20Rule%20of%20Law%20and%20its%20dignity%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFeared%20that%20this%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Court%3B%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EWhere%20the%20Bar%20has%20not%20performed%20the%20duty%20independently%20and%20has%20become%20a%20sycophant%20that%20ultimately%20results%20in%20the%20denigrating%20of%20the%20judicial%20system%20and%20judiciary%20itself.%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20must%20place%20on%20regret%20that%20I%20have%20to%20take%20recourse%20to%20writing%20this%20open%20letter%20as%20the%20efforts%20by%20some%20of%20us%20to%20meet%20you%20personally%20have%20not%20yielded%20any%20result%2C%20despite%20of%20appointment%20having%20been%20sought%20months%20ago%20by%20a%20Senior%20and%20Respected%20colleague%20for%20and%20on%20behalf%20of%20many%20of%20us.%20I%20personally%20met%20the%20Secretary%20General%20and%20apprised%20him%20of%20the%20anxiety%20and%20misgivings%20of%20the%20bar%20in%20this%20regard.%20Emails%20sent%20to%20Registrar%20(J-I)%20by%20Advocates%20on%20Record%20(AoRs)%20making%20serious%20grievance%20about%20it%20have%20not%20been%20responded%2C%20far%20from%20course%20correction%20taking%20place.%20Rules%20of%202013%20provide%20an%20appeal%20to%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Chamber%20Judge%20in%20such%20matters.%20Perhaps%20to%20avoid%20such%20appeals%20being%20filed%20the%20Registrar%20(J%20-I)%20are%20refusing%20anything%20in%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESir%2C%20this%20does%20not%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20Institution%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20under%20your%20Leadership.%20The%20Institution%20is%20highly%20respected%20by%20all.%20That%20respect%20must%20continue%20forever%2C%20in%20all%20respects.%20I%20would%20therefore%20urge%20you%20to%20look%20into%20this%20immediately%20and%20take%20corrective%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYour%20Sincerely%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDushyant%20Dave%20(Senior%20Advocate%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India)%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701844210000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F15192233%2F2022_11img14_Nov_2022_PTI11_14_2022_000176B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fsc-registry-isnt-listing-cases-the-way-it-is-supposed-to-a-letter-to-the-cji%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dushyant%20Dave%20has%20appealed%20to%20the%20CJI%20to%20look%20into%20these%20matters%2C%20particularly%20the%20re-assignment%20of%20important%20cases%2C%20and%20intervene.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fsc-registry-isnt-listing-cases-the-way-it-is-supposed-to-a-letter-to-the-cji%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ready%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%20Elections%2C%20Onus%20on%20Election%20Commission%20to%20Announce%20Schedule%3A%20Centre%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F13152628%2F3475958106_0cdd457c3a_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Union%20government%20told%20the%20parliament%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20December%205%2C%20that%20it%20is%20ready%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20it%20is%20for%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20announce%20the%20schedule%20whenever%20it%20feels%20appropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20ready%20for%20elections%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20ask%20the%20EC%20for%20it%20as%20it%20is%20an%20independent%20constitutional%20body%20and%20only%20it%20can%20decide%20when%20to%20hold%20polls%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Jitendra%20Singh%2C%20a%20junior%20minister%20in%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20(PMO)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fready-for-jk-polls-up-to-ec-to-decide-on-date-government-in-lok-sabha%2Farticleshow%2F105763889.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%3Cem%3E%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20told%20the%20parliament%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20ensured%20that%20the%20country%20has%20just%20one%20flag%20and%20one%20constitution%20as%20opposition%20members%20clashed%20with%20treasury%20benches%20over%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%E2%80%99s%20remark%20was%20during%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%20and%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Reorganisation%20(Amendment)%20Bill.%20He%20countered%20Trinamool%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20(TMC)%20Saugata%20Roy%20who%20had%20said%20%E2%80%9Cone%20flag%2C%20one%20prime%20minister%2C%20one%20constitution%E2%80%9D%20is%20the%20political%20slogan%20of%20the%20BJP.%20Shah%20wondered%20how%20a%20country%20could%20have%20two%20prime%20ministers%2C%20two%20constitutions%2C%20and%20two%20flags.%20He%20added%20that%20it%20is%20not%20merely%20a%20political%20slogan%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20but%20his%20party%20firmly%20believes%20in%20the%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhosoever%20did%20it%20was%20wrong.%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20corrected%20it.%20Your%20approval%20or%20disagreement%20does%20not%20matter.%20The%20entire%20country%20wanted%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20countered%20Roy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMembers%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%20questioned%20the%20government%20over%20introducing%20amendments%20to%20the%20Bill%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20yet%20to%20deliver%20its%20verdict%20on%20the%20Article%20370%20case.%20The%20apex%20court%20concluded%2016%20days%20of%20hearings%20in%20the%20case%20in%20September.%20The%20court%20is%20expected%20to%20pronounce%20its%20verdict%20sometime%20this%20month.%20Article%20370%20gave%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20the%20power%20to%20have%20a%20separate%20constitution%2C%20a%20state%20flag%2C%20and%20autonomy%20of%20internal%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20National%20Conference%20MP%20Hasnain%20Masoodi%20sought%20to%20know%20from%20the%20government%20why%20did%20it%20not%20conduct%20elections%20if%20felt%20the%20situation%20was%20peaceful%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%20He%20alleged%20that%20no%20attempt%20was%20made%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20restore%20statehood%20as%20promised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20legislature%20in%202018%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%20has%20been%20under%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%2C%20prompting%20local%20political%20parties%20to%20demand%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20resume%20electoral%20activities%20in%20the%20Union%20territory.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20official%20statements%2C%20the%20delay%20is%20due%20to%20Bharatiya%20Janta%20Party%20(BJP)%E2%80%99s%20local%20unit%20wanting%20to%20defer%20the%20exercise%20at%20least%20till%20the%202024%20parliamentary%20polls%2C%20as%20it%20is%20not%20yet%20ready%20to%20face%20any%20polls%20even%20local%20body%20polls%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C